bomb
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:an old car in disrepair (in post-1960 use occas. transf. to any old movable mechanical object, e.g. `My old bomb of a lawnmower.').
Origin: [none]
Register: informal
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Usually in phrase "old bomb"; ca1951: heard once in Wellington -->1957 p.c. R. Mason `No doubt older than the 1950s.'
Citations
